<p>Lebanon’s President Joseph Aoun said Beirut is ready to negotiate with Israel to reach an agreement that would end Israeli strikes [thehindu.com#1][newarab.com#1]. He also said the state must have a monopoly on weapons in southern Lebanon, including south of the Litani River, urged international oversight, and stated that Lebanese troops are prepared to deploy at points from which Israeli forces withdraw [timesofisrael.com#1][thehindu.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/YTOBHvqw24V4zF8rb9lqpDQBfKsj4v_vO9oYZ36vcfSaDFaj-YgdHBiwTjz4e3TPICaFJLEz3y4X6A0Irt76LvAspypDmTCQrDBM3LbGN149c6cxJWKz9MqaJjWblz-6M0MmL55PHC_m92pMP1YdaWuto0WkUrDf7mKBq_3BP6IKOh3s5CZPEvwYjAlriHQrW5YZdWsODKxDx8B8xJWU-ryju0ZUOdF0cByROuZzs2McHZor3Zs4aqz2sOGnJMEqWK0h--hiELR5fl4MT0OjxRco' alt='Lebanon signals readiness to negotiate as tensions with Israel continue.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>State control: Aoun said a state monopoly on weapons is needed in southern Lebanon, specifically south of the Litani River [timesofisrael.com#1]</li><li>Negotiation offer: Beirut is ready to negotiate an agreement intended to halt Israeli strikes [thehindu.com#1][newarab.com#1]</li><li>Army deployment: Lebanese troops are prepared to deploy wherever Israeli forces pull back [thehindu.com#1]</li><li>International role: Aoun urged international oversight in the south amid Israeli strikes targeting Hezbollah and Hamas [timesofisrael.com#1]</li><li>Disarmament stance: He reiterated Lebanon’s commitment to disarming militant groups [newarab.com#1]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Lebanese presidency: Seeks negotiations with Israel, a state monopoly on weapons south of the Litani River, and international oversight, with the army ready to deploy in areas of Israeli withdrawal [thehindu.com#1][newarab.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1] (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/lebanon-ready-to-negotiate-to-reach-an-agreement-that-would-end-israeli-strikes-president-says/article70309280.ece'>Mul